original_title: Queens: Dry Harbor Road - Furmanville Avenue
text:
Dry Harbor Road (left not shown) west side, south of Furmanville Avenue, showing the old Methodist burying ground and site of the old Methodist meeting house of 1852. Most of the markers have fallen, some are broken, a few of them remain standing. One reads Susannah Calyer died 1839, age 3 years. In the background the writer believes is 79th Place showing houses thereon looking south from Furmanville Avenue. The cemetery property is now 1927, occupied by frame homes. One Burkhard owned it (cemetery) in 1909.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

Dry Harbor Road, west side, between 84th Street (left) and 80th Street (right) showing in three views an old house of which the following were the owners: - C. Westlake, 1852; F. Trippe, 1860; J. Treppe, 1873; and F. Kochesberger from 1891-1896. This house does not appear in the 1929 Queens Atlas.

April 1923
